examples.en: We copy instinctively the voices of our companions.
His abilities shine out when compared to his companions.
Coker, with two companions, stood by the tailboard of one.
That singularity distinguished him from all his companions.
Mike and his drinking companions began on their third bottle.
The boy claimed that he had been led on by his criminal companions.
See if you can make the prisoner cough up the names of his companions.
It is difficult to disentangle your children from unsuitable companions.
The youth was trying to escape the clutches of two drunken female companions.
The thief gave his companions away (to the police), hoping to escape punishment.
The prisoner hoped to gain his own freedom by informing on his companions in the robbery.
We began to explore the hither bank while our companions crossed the creek to explore the yonder bank.
